"{\"uid\": \"lbc.co.uk-article-france-foils-two-terror-plots-targeting-paris-olympics-5Hjcn9K_2\", \"text\": \"By Danielle de Wolfe  French police have foiled two separate terror plots targeting this summer's Olympic Games in Paris, the government said.  France's interior minister, G\\u00c3\\u00a9rald Darmanin, said that police inParishad carried out \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cseveral arrests\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d linked to two separate plots.  It comes ahead of both the 2024 Paris Olympic games, which kick off on July 24, and the nation's Bastille Day celebrations, which take place on July 14.  France's security has remained at its highest threat level since March, when Islamic State terrorists targeted a Russian concert hall, killing 145.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIn recent days, we have not made it public because we are in an election campaign, but we have arrested people who may have planned and put terrorist attacks into place,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Mr Darmanin said in an interview on Friday.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThey are being handed over to the justice services at this very moment\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d, he added.  The nature of the plots and details of the threats has so far not been revealed by the French government.  It comes as France prepares to navigate security threats surrounding the upcoming Paris Olympics, with the opening ceremony taking place along the River Seine, which runs through the heart of the city.  Read more:Keir Starmer holds first cabinet meeting as PM sets out Labour's mandate for change  Read more:Joe Biden vows he's still running in presidential election and plays down disastrous debate with Trump as 'bad episode'  It follows comments from the French interior minister, who admitted that more than 50 French parliamentary candidates and activists had been attacked over the course of campaigning ahead of national elections.  According to the minister, 51 verbal and physical attacks had been registered targetting candidates, their deputies or supporters during campaigning.  Tomorrow marks the final round of voting in the country's national election, with President  Emmanuel Macron mirroring PM Rishi Sunak's decision to call a snap election - despite his position looking increasingly precarious.  It comes amid increasing pressure from far right leader Marine Le Pen.  France's civil unrest follows what's been described as 'civil war', with mass protests taking place across the country following President Macron's surprise announcement on June 9.  England and Scotland both facing tricky opponents in their bid for football immortality  56m ago  England found their rivals in belligerent mood as Mitchell Starc tallied up the runs - eventually caught for 77 by Stokes as Australia approached 500  2h ago  The bank will no longer allow staff to don the festive knitwear this Christmas  6h ago  The treatment is suitable for men whose cancer has not spread outside of the prostate gland or has spread to the area just outside the gland  10h ago  It comes after Ireland, the Netherlands, Spain and Slovenia pulled out of the singing competition  13h ago  An investigation from the Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman found that doctors at the Countess of Chester Hospital showed a \\\"worrying lack of accountability\\\" and failed to keep proper records  13h ago  Thomas Tuchel's England may have to do it the hard way as the World Cup draw put them on a collision course with several major nations  14h ago  The bank will no longer allow staff to don the festive knitwear this Christmas  6h ago  An investigation from the Parliamentary and Health Service Ombudsman found that doctors at the Countess of Chester Hospital showed a \\\"worrying lack of accountability\\\" and failed to keep proper records  13h ago  A teenager who got out of an ambulance on a motorway was then Tasered by police before being hit by a car and killed, the police watchdog said.  21h ago  An NHS nurse who was suspended for calling a transgender paedophile \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cMr\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d has been left in legal limbo as the Government delays publishing equalities guidance.  1d ago  Caz describes London as a city plagued by homelessness, knife crime, drug dealers, pickpockets and phone snatching  1d ago  London schools took half of the top 20 spots for comprehensives in the rankings, and 12 of the top-ranked state primary schools  1d ago  Rightmove said residents of Skipton ranked it particularly highly for its access to nature and green spaces, the friendliness of the people, and access to essential services such as schools  1d ago  Follow us:  About & Help  Get The LBC App  Legal & Info  Business & Careers  \\u00c2\\u00a9 Global 2025 | 30 Leicester Square, London, WC2H 7LA  Copyright Global 2025. 30 Leicester Square, London. W C 2 H 7 L A.\"}"